<span id="freeTextContainer14013900362257588345">In this novel brother Cadfael investigates the death by poison of a wealthy landowner who has recently retired into the wall of the Benedictine abbey with the promise of bequeathing his estate to the monks. The case is complicated by the fact that the widow is Cadfael&apos;s former lover. Meanwhile the possible appointment of a new abbot brings further concerns for the brothers.<br/><br/>I liked this book a lot more than the previous ones in this series, Brother Cadfael is really growing on me. The audio versi</span>
  <span id="freeText14013900362257588345" style="display:none">In this novel brother Cadfael investigates the death by poison of a wealthy landowner who has recently retired into the wall of the Benedictine abbey with the promise of bequeathing his estate to the monks. The case is complicated by the fact that the widow is Cadfael's former lover. Meanwhile the possible appointment of a new abbot brings further concerns for the brothers.<br /><br />I liked this book a lot more than the previous ones in this series, Brother Cadfael is really growing on me. The audio version read by Patrick Tull is excellent (his narration is on the slow side, a speed adjustment to 1.2 made it perfect for me :). 3.5 stars</span>
