  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2062113800" />
    <a title="Laura Anderson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/59534250-laura-anderson"><img alt="Laura Anderson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1473617792p2/59534250.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2062113800?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura Anderson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura Anderson" href="/user/show/59534250-laura-anderson">Laura Anderson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/59534250-laura-anderson?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/59534250-laura-anderson?shelf=mystery-detective">mystery-detective</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/59534250-laura-anderson?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2062113800" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4758440447291103324">Another day, another Cadfael book read! Apparently I&apos;m addicted. It only took 2 and a Kindle Unlimited trial.<br/><br/>This had a really good story, bustling central mystery and memorable characters. I particularly liked the exploration of the recklessness of youth, and how we have to live with the consequences of hasty or poor decisions made. I also love the touches of Welsh culture and history in these books - missed it in book 2. Will totally read the next one.</span>
  <span id="freeText4758440447291103324" style="display:none">Another day, another Cadfael book read! Apparently I'm addicted. It only took 2 and a Kindle Unlimited trial.<br /><br />This had a really good story, bustling central mystery and memorable characters. I particularly liked the exploration of the recklessness of youth, and how we have to live with the consequences of hasty or poor decisions made. I also love the touches of Welsh culture and history in these books - missed it in book 2. Will totally read the next one.</span>
